# HTTP client

## Rule

Use the **`HttpClient`** from `@repo/api` (`packages/api/src/helpers/http-client.helper.ts`, exported as `httpClient`) for **all outbound HTTP calls** in this monorepo: JSON APIs, FormSubmit, webhooks, and third-party REST endpoints.

Do **not**:

- use global **`fetch`** for application HTTP (except where the platform offers no alternative and the rule owner approves an exception),
- call **`axios`** directly in app or package code,
- add parallel HTTP stacks.

## Pattern

```typescript
import { httpClient } from "./http-client.helper";
// In other packages: import { httpClient } from "@repo/api"

const response = await httpClient.post<{ message?: string }>({
  url: "https://example.com/api",
  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json", Accept: "application/json" },
  body: payload,
});

// response.status, response.data — validateStatus allows any status; check status explicitly
```

## Helpers

Domain-specific helpers (e.g. `postFormSubmitAjax` in `form-submit.helper.ts`) should wrap `httpClient` and keep URLs and body shapes in one place.

## NestJS services

Backend code may use Nest `HttpService` only if it is the established pattern for that app; otherwise prefer the same `HttpClient` helper for consistency when calling external services from Node.
